column14: Cell A1 always must contain the dimensions of the pipette tool. This is validated against the tool.
Row 1 starting at column B is reserved for the plate column labels but is not required. Just there for readability.
Column A starting at row 2 is reserved for the plate row labels but is not required. Just there for readability.
Individual well command format: <Destination well>;<Volume>;<lead air gap>;<trailing air gap>;<VVP residual volume>
Separator hierarchy is comma between channel instructions and a semi-colon (;) between dispense parameters.
An empty entry or a volume that is less than or equal to 0 means no channel operation will occur.
All destination well names will be validated against the destination plate.
